{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/2014-02-03-staircase-climbing-with-1-or-2-steps/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><strong>You are climbing a stair case. Each time you can either make 1 step or 2 steps. The staircase has n steps. In how many distinct ways can you climb the staircase?</strong></p>\n<p>This problem has a dynamic programming solution with the following recurrence:<code class=\"language-text\">L[i] = L[i-1] + L[i-2]</code> where L[i] stores the number of distinct ways to climb i stairs. Solution has O(n) complexity.</p>\n<p>We can make two observations:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>We can solve this problem with O(1) space complexity;</li>\n<li>This is the Fibonacci recurrence.</li>\n</ol>\n<div id=\"codeSnippetWrapper\">\n<div id=\"codeSnippet\" style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\">\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum1\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   1:</span> <span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">int</span> stairs(<span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">int</span> n) {</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum2\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   2:</span>   <span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">if</span> (n == 0)</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum3\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   3:</span>     <span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">return</span> 0;</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum4\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   4:</span>   <span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">int</span> a = 1;</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum5\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   5:</span>   <span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">int</span> b = 1;</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum6\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   6:</span>   <span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">for</span> (<span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">int</span> i = 1; i &lt; n; i++) {</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum7\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   7:</span>     <span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">int</span> c = a;</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum8\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   8:</span>     a = b;</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum9\" style=\"color:#606060;\">   9:</span>     b += c;</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum10\" style=\"color:#606060;\">  10:</span>   }</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum11\" style=\"color:#606060;\">  11:</span>   <span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">return</span> b;</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n<pre style=\"overflow:visible;font-size:8pt;font-family:'Courier New', courier, monospace;color:black;direction:ltr;text-align:left;margin:0;line-height:12pt;width:100%;background-color:#f4f4f4;border-style:none;padding:0;\"><span id=\"lnum12\" style=\"color:#606060;\">  12:</span> }</pre>\n<p><!--CRLF--></p>\n</div>\n</div>","excerpt":"You are climbing a stair case. Each time you can either make 1 step or 2 steps. The staircase has n steps. In how many distinct ways can you climb the staircaseâ€¦","frontmatter":{"date":"03 February, 2014","path":"/blog/2014-02-03-staircase-climbing-with-1-or-2-steps/","title":"Staircase climbing with 1 or 2 steps"},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"2 min read"}}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864","63159454"]}